5480	SeanSherlock	Labour	15092.0	Cork East	speech	unknown-language	2014-04-02 00:00:00	Ceisteanna - Questions	150	" I move amendment No. 186: In page 673, line 37, to delete “fine not exceeding €1,000” and substitute “class D fine”. The function of this amendment is to take account of the fact that ""not exceeding €1,000"" fine formulations are now dealt with by the “class D"" fine in the Fines Act 2010. This section provides that if the contravention in respect of which a person is convicted of an offence under this Bill is continued after the conviction, the person shall be guilty of a further offence on every day on which the contravention continues. This derives from section 240(6) of the Companies Act 1990."
